title: The Langham. Central Park West, Seventy-third to Seventy-fourth Street.

text:
Central Park West, west side, north from 73rd Street. A detail of the Dakota Apartments (built between 1879 and 1885, and still standing in 1935) is shown at the extreme left. It is followed by the Langham, the San Remo (now replaced by a new apartment house with the same name), and the Kennilworth. About 1922.

Gift of E. M. Jenks.
